\f0\b \cf2 Question
\f1\b0 : I have been training Bjj for a while. I have made some pretty good advancement. However, instead of being motivated, I am having a hard time even thinkning about BJJ. I tried not training. I have tried extra hard training( I went to ATT for a week). Have you ever had problems staying motivated? And if so, what have you done to get over it?\
\
\

\f0\b Answer
\f1\b0 : Over the years, there were numerous times when I lacked motivation for training. Sometimes, these periods lasted for a couple of weeks. At other times, they lasted for a few months. And still other times, it lasted for over one year.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\cf2 What you must realize is that these periods of "feeling unmotivated" happen to everyone. So, you are not alone.\
You must also understand that this is a phase you are going through, and that more than likely, at some point in time, you will move beyond this phase. And, if you do not move beyond this phase after a few years, you must accept this change as a part of your future.\
The bottom line is this: Worry not about tomorrow, for none of us are promised tomorrow! Enjoy life today!\
Since your mind and heart have no desire to focus on Jiu Jitsu, focus on other activities that bring fulfillment and enjoyment to your life! If Jiu Jitsu comes back into the picture at some point in time, cool. If it doesn't, that's cool as well.........as long as you have enjoyed life along the way!\
Does this all make sense?\
Enjoy life my brother!\
Roy Harris\cf0 \
